     Employment Information

    The Northampton VAMC provides tertiary psychiatric, substance abuse,
    and PTSD services as well as primary and secondary levels of medical
     care to a veteran population in western Massachusetts of more than
   85,000 men and women. Primary emphasis is placed on continuity of care
       from hospital to the community through community care centers,
      outpatient treatment, and vocational rehabilitation. There is an
   extensive network of residential settings from board and care homes to
      skilled nursing care. The Northampton VAMC has affiliations with
     schools in dentistry, nursing, psychology, optometry, occupational
         therapy, social work, and pharmacy, as well as other health
                     professional and technical fields.

